===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|uncountable|biology}} Conditions suitable for an organism or population of organisms to live.
#: ''This park offers important amphibian '''habitat''' and breeding area.''
# {{lb|en|countable|biology}} A place or type of site where an organism or population naturally occurs.
# {{lb|en|countable|biology}} A terrestrial or aquatic area distinguished by geographic, abiotic and biotic features, whether entirely natural or semi-natural.
#* {{quote-book|title=The Ecology of Transportation|page=248|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1402045042|author=John Davenport, ‎Julia L. Davenport|year=2006
|passage=rights-of-way are usually perceived as disturbance zones that provide a '''habitat''' and corridor for non-native species.}}
# A place in which a person lives.
